Pico 4 active firmware: smart film and oven knob puzzle.

Hardware:
- GPIO 15 / physical pin 20: smart film relay/driver input
- GPIO 16 / physical pin 21: smart film attention buzzer driver input
- GPIO 18 / physical pin 24: electromagnetic lock relay/driver input
- GPIO 26 / ADC0 / physical pin 31: oven potentiometer wiper

Main topics:
- Publishes escape/pico4/smart_film_ready
- Publishes escape/pico4/oven_position_update
- Publishes escape/pico4/oven_target_reached
- Publishes escape/pico4/electromag_lock_unlocked
- Publishes escape/pico4/oven_error
- Subscribes escape/cmd/pico4/reveal_smart_film
- Subscribes escape/cmd/pico4/arm_oven_potentiometer
- Subscribes escape/cmd/pico4/unlock_electromag_lock
- Subscribes escape/cmd/all/status_request
- Subscribes escape/cmd/all/reset_puzzle

The oven potentiometer is inactive until the Raspberry Pi arms it with
escape/cmd/pico4/arm_oven_potentiometer after the color button code is solved.

The lock only releases after:
- the oven potentiometer has been armed
- potentiometer-derived value stays at 350 within tolerance for the configured hold time

The potentiometer maps to a 170-440 degree oven range in 15-degree steps
anchored at 170, so 350 remains an exact reachable value.

After the oven reaches 350, Pico 4 keeps the electromagnetic lock released
until the room reset command arrives. The Raspberry Pi watches for the dial to
return to 170 for the room reset, but only after the room has been complete for
the configured safety delay.

The small LED thermometer strip is not used in the current build. Pico 4 publishes
the simulated oven temperature to MQTT for the Raspberry Pi controller and fire panel.
